Package: rdtp
Title: RD Tipping-Point Cutoff Search for Discrete Forcing Variables
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: person("Andrew", "McEachin", role = c("aut", "cre"),
                  email = "andrew.mceachin@gmail.com")
Description: Searches over candidate cutoff values on a discrete running
    variable to find, for each unit, the cutoff that maximizes R-squared
    from a linear-spline regression discontinuity (RD) regression.
    Implements the threshold-detection method from McEachin, Domina, and
    Penner (2020, <doi:10.1002/pam.22202>) for settings where the true
    cutoff is unknown and varies across units (e.g., schools, counties).
    Supports OLS, heteroskedasticity-robust, and cluster-robust standard
    errors. Depends only on base R; robust/cluster SEs use 'sandwich'
    when available.
License: GPL (>= 3) + file LICENSE
URL: https://github.com/amceachin-code/rdtp
BugReports: https://github.com/amceachin-code/rdtp/issues
Encoding: UTF-8
Depends: R (>= 3.5.0)
Imports: stats
